From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <noreply@example.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 22:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: default priv->xsk_max_qbands=4 at probe

Per spec §5.1, priv->xsk_max_qbands is zero-initialised at probe time and
was meant to be set by a flavor module's pcd_ops->install callback. The
current Phase-2 skeleton af_xdp_pool.ko only registers qmgmt_ops (no
pcd_ops), so xsk_max_qbands stays 0 and every bind(XDP_ZEROCOPY) hits the
queue_id validator in 0075a (queue_id >= priv->xsk_max_qbands -> -EINVAL)
even when the caller passes a valid qid.

Default xsk_max_qbands to DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS (4) at probe so the
M2 (qmgmt-only) DUT verification gate can clear bind(). A future flavor
module that registers pcd_ops may refine this value downward based on
CEETM/PCD topology.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <noreply@example.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index 0000000000cc..0000000000dd 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -3474,6 +3474,12 @@ static int dpaa_eth_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	priv->msg_enable = netif_msg_init(debug, DPAA_MSG_DEFAULT);
 
+	/* Default to spec-max qbands so M2 (qmgmt-only) bind() can pass the
+	 * queue_id validator before any pcd_ops->install runs. A flavor
+	 * module's pcd_ops->install may later refine this downward.
+	 */
+	priv->xsk_max_qbands = DPAA1_XSK_MAX_QBANDS;
+
 	priv->egress_fqs = devm_kcalloc(dev, dpaa_max_num_txqs(),
 					sizeof(*priv->egress_fqs),
 					GFP_KERNEL);
-- 
